re `back-to-back' pairs out-of-plane,\nmimicking a CME signal, or a concave $R_{\\Psi_2}(\\Delta S)$. Supplemental\nstudies of $R_{\\Psi_3}(\\Delta S)$ in terms of the triangular flow ($v_3$),\nwhere only backgrounds exist but any CME would average to zero, are also\npresented.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Mar 2018 19:52:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 May 2018 04:21:12 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 30 Aug 2018 17:20:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-11"}
